  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-12-06",
    "date": "2007-12-20T19:09:09Z",
    "text": "Advocates Dedicated to Older Child Parental Tax Credit (ADOPT) Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a $2,000 tax credit for costs associated with the adoption of a child who has reached nine years of age before the adoption decree becomes final. Allows the credit each year until such child attains the age of 19."
